cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.RO, cs.SD 

The paper discusses the evolution of methods for analyzing first person vision videos, which involves computer vision and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also discusses user-machine interaction, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of wearable technologies and action cameras also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The challenges and opportunities discussed in the paper also relate to robotics (cs.RO) and statistical learning (cs.SD).
